text: Kul-Kanas () is a rural locality (a selo) in Karanovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 209 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 40 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 4 km from Karan-Kunkas. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Kul-Kanas
